CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 15, 1946, pg. 17, reads: "Checking Up - Dr. Charles J. Burke, an ex-Army captain...'Tuesday doctor' at the IKS Maternity Clinic, checks up on one of the youngsters to see that the ticker is in shape. The...conducted by the University of Pittsburgh Medical School and is maintained for needy mothers and their babies.  The Public Health Nursing Service also cooperates in sponsorship of the clinic, which is held Tuesdays, Thursdays and Fridays,  Left to right: Mrs. Phyllis Thomas, Dr. Burke examining the infant, and Miss Frances Patterson. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of nurses Phyllis Thomas and Frances Patterson standing on either side of Dr. Charles Burks or Burke, examining baby with stethoscope, in Irene Kaufmann Settlement Maternity Clinic
